# Custom environment variables & secrets for your app.
#
# Substrait reads this file when you upload the app and PRE-CREATES each entry under
# the app's Settings (Environment variables / Secrets), so after uploading you just
# fill in the real values in the portal — no redeploy needed for the values to apply.
#
#   NAME=value            → an environment variable, prefilled with `value`
#   NAME=value   # secret → a secret (write-only; masked in the portal)
#
# Notes:
#   - The value after `=` is the prefilled placeholder (may be left empty).
#   - Quote values that contain a literal `#` so it isn't read as a comment.
#   - DO NOT list DATABASE_URL, REDIS_URL or JWT_SECRET — the platform injects those.
#   - Read these at runtime from the environment (os.getenv); never commit real secrets.
#   - Re-uploading never overwrites a value you've already set in the portal.

# Example plain config:
APP_GREETING=Hello from Substrait

# Example secret (leave blank; set the real key in the portal after upload):
THIRD_PARTY_API_KEY=   # secret
